commentTextItems.html: wide outside the off, lofted over extra covers

commentPostTextItems.html: the usual crowd rushing into the ground
that is it. the game is over
Match State: West Indies won by 8 wickets

commentTextItems.html: so wide outside the off, if it were not ball the noball call, it would have been a wide
right on the slot, launches into the ball, takes it way over long on!

commentPostTextItems.html: that ball went soaring over hospitality tent, into the car park
new ball being selected as we lost the previous ball

commentTextItems.html: well pitched up. mistimed but lara goes for the shot anyway, over midoff
slightly short, pulled over midon
a better shot now! played neatly between cover and midoff

commentPostTextItems.html: now, that is better batting. no need to slog. he could play proper cricketing shots like this

commentTextItems.html: outside the off. Lara thinks he is a pinch hitter. swishes the bat and misses
on the stumps, played back to the bowler
way down the offside
on the stumps. pushed to covers for a quick single

commentPostTextItems.html: all rounder Hamilton with the ball now

commentTextItems.html: outside th eoff, Lara slogs rather unnecessarily and misses. declared a wide

commentTextItems.html: well outside the off. Lara plays a rank ugly shot trying to pull it to midwicket. gets only an inside edge
outside the off, pulled to midon. He didn't time that properly as well
tries a pull and mistimes, safely over square leg
outside the off, beaten trying to run the ball to thirdman
outside the off, goes for a big shot on the off, under edged to second slip
lofted over midon

commentPostTextItems.html: West Indies know that they want to score runs quickly

milestones.description: Hamilton and Asim Butt's 20-run partnership is SCOT's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 11 between Hamilton and Asim Butt
John Blain has become the top wicket-taker for SCOT in ODIs with 7 wickets, going past Nick Dyer's 5
Asim Butt has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4) for SCOT, going past John Blain
